{"id": "duc04-testb-2:8#24", "contents": "International Olympic Committee (IOC) President Juan Antonio Samaranch addressed the allegations of corruption within the organization, stating that any members found guilty of accepting bribes would be expelled. He announced that a special IOC panel would investigate the claims, which were made by senior Swiss member Marc Hodler. Samaranch emphasized the IOC's commitment to protecting its integrity and the integrity of the Olympics, saying, \"If we have to clean, we will clean... After, the IOC will be even stronger than before.\" He expressed surprise at Hodler's allegations and suggested that Hodler should have brought his concerns to the IOC executive board first."}
